4. Specification of the DHCP client-serv:
{
    "4.4.3 Initialization with an externally assigned network address": [
        {
            "Original": "The client sends a DHCPINFORM message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client may request specific configuration parameters by including the 'parameter request list' option.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client generates and records a random transaction identifier and inserts that identifier into the 'xid' field.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client places its own network address in the 'ciaddr' field.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client SHOULD NOT request lease time parameters.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The client then unicasts the DHCPINFORM to the DHCP server if it knows the server's address, otherwise it broadcasts the message to the limited (all 1s) broadcast address.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "DHCPINFORM messages MUST be directed to the 'DHCP server' UDP port.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Once a DHCPACK message with an 'xid' field matching that in the client's DHCPINFORM message arrives from any server, the client is initialized.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "If the client does not receive a DHCPACK within a reasonable period of time (60 seconds or 4 tries if using timeout suggested insection 4.1), then it SHOULD display a message informing the user of the problem, and then SHOULD begin network processing using suitable defaults as per Appendix A.",
            "Adjusted": "If the client does not receive a DHCPACK within a reasonable period of time (60 seconds or 4 tries if using timeout suggested in section 4.1), then the client SHOULD display a message informing the user of the problem, and then SHOULD begin network processing using suitable defaults as per Appendix A."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "4.4 DHCP client behavior": [
        {
            "Original": "Figure 5 gives a state-transition diagram for a DHCP client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A client can receive the following messages from a server: o DHCPOFFER o DHCPACK o DHCPNAK The DHCPINFORM message is not shown in figure 5.",
            "Adjusted": "A client can receive the following messages from a server: DHCPOFFER, DHCPACK, and DHCPNAK. The DHCPINFORM message is not shown in Figure 5."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A client simply sends the DHCPINFORM and waits for DHCPACK messages.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Once the client has selected its parameters, it has completed the configuration process.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Table 5 gives the use of the fields and options in a DHCP message by a client.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The remainder of this section describes the action of the DHCP client for each possible incoming message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The description in the following section corresponds to the full configuration procedure previously described insection 3.1, and the text in the subsequent section corresponds to the abbreviated configuration procedure described in section 3.2.",
            "Adjusted": "The description in the following section corresponds to the full configuration procedure previously described in section 3.1, and the text in the subsequent section corresponds to the abbreviated configuration procedure described in section 3.2."
        },
        {
            "Original": "\\-------- ------- | | +-------------------------->| |<\\-------------------+ | INIT- | | +-------------------->| INIT | | | REBOOT |DHCPNAK/ +---------->| |<\\---+ | | |Restart| | ------- | | \\-------- | DHCPNAK/ | | | | Discard offer | -/Send DHCPDISCOVER | -/Send DHCPREQUEST | | | | | | DHCPACK v | | \\----------- | (not accept.)/ ----------- | | | | | Send DHCPDECLINE | | | | REBOOTING | | | | SELECTING |<\\----+ | | | | / | | |DHCPOFFER/ | \\----------- | / ----------- | |Collect | | | / | | | replies | DHCPACK/ | / +----------------+ +-------+ | Record lease, set| | v Select offer/ | timers T1, T2 ------------ send DHCPREQUEST | | | +----->| | DHCPNAK, Lease expired/ | | | | REQUESTING | Halt network | DHCPOFFER/ | | | | Discard ------------ | | | | | | ----------- | | +--------+ DHCPACK/ | | | | Record lease, set -----| REBINDING | | | timers T1, T2 / | | | | | DHCPACK/ ----------- | | v Record lease, set ^ | +----------------> \\------- /timers T1,T2 | | +----->| |<\\---+ | | | | BOUND |<\\---+ | | DHCPOFFER, DHCPACK, | | | T2 expires/ DHCPNAK/ DHCPNAK/Discard ------- | Broadcast Halt network | | | | DHCPREQUEST | +-------+ | DHCPACK/ | | T1 expires/ Record lease, set | | Send DHCPREQUEST timers T1, T2 | | to leasing server | | | | ---------- | | | | |------------+ | +->| RENEWING | | | |----------------------------+ \\---------- Figure 5: State-transition diagram for DHCP clients",
            "Adjusted": "Figure 5 shows a state-transition diagram for DHCP clients."
